{
  "number": 2742,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2742",
  "title": "Feature: Return helpers in hits > empty template",
  "body": "The use case is to display certain text only if there was a `query` given for a search, otherwise display a different message. Outside of using a closure there's no helpful methods. \r\n\r\nFor example. the `Toggle` widget has a `isRefined` parameter that is passed to the template so you can use it like so:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{{#isRefined}}checked{{/isRefined}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be great to have a few like this for the hit>empty template to use like so..\r\n\r\n```js\r\nNo recipes were found with that criteria {{#hasQuery}}matching the search term{{query}}{{/hasQuery}}\r\n```",
